<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,568,649,675]" box="[151,568,649,675]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,568,649,675]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,568,649,675]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Bigot, 1859" authorityName="Bigot" authorityYear="1859" box="[237,568,649,675]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Heteropsilopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[237,419,649,675]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Heteropsilopus</emphasis>
Bigot, 1859
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,719,888]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
This genus has been reported from 
<collectingRegion box="[570,655,720,743]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[674,746,719,744]" name="China" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">China</collectingCountry>
), southern 
<collectingCountry box="[877,937,719,744]" name="India" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[953,1055,719,744]" name="Australia" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Australia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1118,1235,719,744]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
. The presence of 
<taxonomicName authority="Liu, Zhu &amp; Yang" authorityName="Liu, Zhu &amp; Yang" box="[151,687,756,781]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Heteropsilopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis box="[151,471,756,780]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Heteropsilopus yunnanensis</emphasis>
Liu, Zhu &amp; Yang
</taxonomicName>
indicates the distribution of the genus might be wider than the previous assumption of Gondwanan origins (
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, X. &amp; Zhu, Y. &amp; Yang, D." box="[661,836,791,816]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="63 - 67" refId="ref24793" refString="Liu, X., Zhu, Y. &amp; Yang, D. (2012) New species of Heteropsilopus and Amblypsilopus from China (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Zootaxa, 3198, 63 - 67." type="journal article" year="2012">
Liu 
<emphasis box="[709,759,792,816]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
). However, no species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bigot" authorityYear="1859" box="[1129,1299,792,816]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Heteropsilopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1129,1299,792,816]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Heteropsilopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found during this research. Diagnosis of the genus is available in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bickel, D. J." box="[840,1000,828,853]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="1 - 394" refId="ref24202" refString="Bickel, D. J. (1994) The Australian Sciapodinae (Diptera: Dolichopodidae), with a review of the Oriental and Australasian faunas, and a world conspectus of the subfamily. Records of the Australian Museum Supplement, 21, 1 - 394. https: // doi. org / 10.3853 / j. 0812 - 7387.21.1994.50" type="journal article" year="1994">Bickel (1994)</bibRefCitation>
, which is mostly based on Australian species.
</paragraph>
